{
  "texts": [
    "Temperature is a measure of the average kinetic energy of the particles in a substance.",
    "At the microscopic level, the atoms or molecules in an object are moving, vibrating, and colliding in complex ways.",
    "Each particle has its own state defined by its position, velocity, and interactions with other particles.",
    "The combination of all these states and their interactions over time is incredibly complex and computationally intensive to model precisely.",
    "However, when we touch an object, our sensory receptors respond to the rate of heat transfer from the object to our skin, which is influenced by the average kinetic energy of the particles in the object."
  ]
}